section.def:
Board
                (上訴委員會) means a Drainage Appeal Board constituted
            under section 30;

mortgage
                (按揭) means a mortgage or charge registrable in
            the Land Registry;

obstruction
                (障礙物) in Parts III and IV includes earth, stone,
            timber and material of all kinds artificially placed in any main watercourse;

Panel
                (上訴委員備選小組) means the panel of persons appointed
            to be the Drainage Appeal Board Panel under section 29(1);

solicitor
                (律師) has the meaning assigned to it in
                section 2 of the Legal Practitioners Ordinance (Cap. 159);

subparagraph.content:
any drain and sewer as defined by section 2 of the Buildings
                        Ordinance (Cap. 123);
                        and

paragraph.content:
receive and consider any material, whether by way of oral evidence, written
                    statements, documents or otherwise, whether or not such material would be
                    admissible in evidence in civil or criminal proceedings;
